<br>
You might already know this, but if not, IF you are in a full group and you start hearing guildchat or ooc about others looking for a group, you know, people will stay with that group, and hardly any leave until the night is late and all are very tired have to go to bed.  Very rarely do people leave a PoP group, before they absolutely have to, because PoP exp and some yard trash loot is very nice and of course the parchments.  <br>
<br>
I have soloed probabably 90 percent plus of my lvl 61 exp.  Before PoP, some in my own guild used to jest in saying they never saw me group outside of raids.  Since PoP, I think I might have soloed 2 or 3 times.  LOL, one night I got a tell from one guild group in PoN.  When I got there, I got invited to a guild group, but didn't realize for a few minutes, it was not the one who invited me to PoN.  During this time of apoligizing to the other group, I got a tell from a non-guild group in PoN and a group in PoJ.  <br>
<br>
Some times I have gone thru a few pop zones with lfg up with no luck, and I head off to kill dark blue lotuses in fg, and within 30 to 60 minutes, I start getting tells from pop groups.<br>
<br>
I never get to solo anymore, hehe.<br>
<br>
Mages are great in my opinion. We have damage, summons, pets dps and one thing I hardly ever see mentioned here, the mala series.  Have you ever seen the enc or sham in your group draw agro and get beat on when the cast slow, tash or other of their debuffs, and I stand there and hardly ever get any agro from malosini or mala, because I have a pet to keep my agro, hehe.  I love it.<br>
<br>
