<br>
Before POP Mage BST pets could tank mobs decently as long as stuff was slowed 50% or better...<br>
<br>
Now even with shamine slow pets get raped insane on those dual 450 hits on even 2nd teir planes.<br>
<br>
I dont have my 60 level slow.. never will but before POP I could at least solo Ahekeva with my 30% slow decently if I could not get a group, which happens 50% of the time.<br>
<br>
Now in POP, at 62 which I had to get to just to get a new pet /RUDE VI for giving even shamans a new pet at 61 and beastlords none.<br>
<br>
ALL of Ahekeva is light blue, most of FG is green , still can't get a damn group in POV or PON <br>
<br>
Stuck soloing light blue stuff in POD at an asanine rate even that stuff toasts the pets while druids and out chariming rats 3 times as good as my pet, or quadding for insane AA in pod pov.<br>
<br>
Pisses me off that the beta testers did not notice and then tell us how gimp pets became in POP.<br>
<br>
Why is it that beastlords and Mages cannot solo effectively anymore and Druids, Wizzies chanters can solo BETTER than they could before.<br>
<br>
Who cares if a pet is level 60 when it has ~500 more hps than the level 47 pet we get at 60.  Pets in pop should have 10k hps minum or some sort of defensive damage mitigation.<br>
<br>
Look at it this way, top mage pets have always had close to what warriors have for unbuffed hps prior to POP.<br>
<br>
Now warriors have 7-8k unbuffed sometimes and pets are sitting below 5k still.   Even if pets had 10k hps at 61+ they still could not tank POV crap anyways, they need far better damage mitigation than we have on them now.<br>
